reviewText: Jazz Legends: Duke Ellington and His Orchestra (1929-1943) is a series of short films made in Hollywood featuring the legendary Duke Ellington performing his biggest hits: Black And Tan (1929), Check and Double Check (1930), Symphony in Black (1934), Paramount Pictoral No. 889 (1937), The Hit Parade of 1937, and RKO Jamboree No. 7 (1943).
